messages.message:
I saw some strange behaviour, happy to see if we can recreate it if required;
I had 2 date fields to extract dates from passports. On the passport it is written like 01 APR/APR 2015, so I asked it to change it to dd/mm/yyyy on the first field. Then the result of the second field changed to this format as well (without me changing the second field). When I then ran the document through the app it would return dd/mm/yyyy for the first field but 01 APR/APR 2015 for the 2nd field.
these are two different fields for the same document, right?
i assume the documents are pretty short if they're passports?
Yes correct, an expiration date and a birthdate. Just rebuild the app on the Commercial UAT and had the exact same situation.

right, then this is probably the one/all field issue in https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05EQQJGN7L/p1696439021398979 ; in which case it should be fixed in 23.41, and idk what's going to happen for 23.39
